he doesnt not do this thing in the house.
za.gər kwa yak kə.si ka.ren bä sram.nzər

from there he will set off to kill people.
si kwa zöb.thə ŋa.zü.bra.kwər war.fo ka.bed.bo
first, he will pray to god (not devil)
and leave the flesh behind for me."
he will point out this man

"take bäi's spirit back and leave his flesh behind for me!"
fə.thə kre.far ka.bef ke.ke kwa sre.mar bä.ne.ma
when he sets off, that man will not see him because ...
mə.nzen fə.thə sra.ru.gər na.gay.ʔə dis.turb ʔor ŋa.re dis.turb sra.rär
in the house when he sleeps, his wife or his children will distract him.

therefore, he will go out to another place in the savannah.
fä ʔa.ne tə.ma.təm kwa ka.be ya.fi.yo.kwər bə.tha zan yəf.nzər
there he will start that action. the spell will hit him.
if a boy (the sorcerer) is from rouku ...
zə.bär kwa yam zä wä.fi.yo.kwər zə.ba kreth.fär sa.fis.fo
he will do this in night and fly from here to safis
bä bə.tha zan sraf.nzər bə.than.me sraf.nzər
the spell would hit him. he will hit him with the magic ...
he would return again in the night.
ke.ke kwa bä sra.ru.gər ʔo sra.wä.kwər
he would not sleep there or stay until sunrise.
zə.bär we kwa ŋan.bri.gwər ke.ke kwa mo.then fi sray.ʔak fi krath.fä.nzər
he will return again in the night. he will not walk on the path, but he will fly.
fə.thə srä.bəth ka.be bə.than zan sreth.käf wa.tik fä ma.ne kwik ʔe.rä fof
when is finishes these things (drinking the body liquid), that is when he starts the magic at him. then they are sick over there.
keke does not negate that sentence (says Nakre). it also forms a separate intonation contour. probably belongs to the previous clause
he does that thing to the wallaby ...

fi ʔa.ne ka.be.ʔa.ne mi.ta.fo kwa wə.thor.thə
but the man's spirit will go inside ...
nä fa.so ro.kar.fo ʔo fəth.zə ŋa.tha zrä.thəb
some (game) animal or wherever. I would go inside a dog.
it can be anything ... a bird.

ne.zä ka.be kwa kwo.si yə ke.ke ŋa.tha kwa kwo.si sra.rä yak.me

how the suffering ... that is when the dogs will suffer ...
and the man will suffer the same way.
kwot ʔe ŋa.tha fə.thə zä kwo.si sra.rä ka.be bä kwa kwo.si yə

bä.ne.ma ŋa.tha ʔa.ne na.fa.ne yəf.kaf səf.rä
because the dog was with his name.
this is how they are doing the magic.
the body liquid that they drink
the strength of the corpse carries them

ʔa.ne kam ʔa.ne tə.mäf kwa yə.zä.nzər
that bones ... that strength will carry him.
the bones and the body liquid.
